body_html:
@parag2489 good question. I may have it incorrect and that's why I created this issue hoping to clarify things. It seems there are a couple styles of preprocessing:

      'cifarnet': cifarnet_preprocessing,
      'inception': inception_preprocessing,
      'resnet_v1_200': vgg_preprocessing,

As found in tensorflow/models#2217 and https://github.com/tensorflow/models/tree/31adae5327c0258ce630f7b3e9f3cf0df78e3ba6/research/slim/preprocessing

body:
@parag2489 good question. I may have it incorrect and that's why I created this issue hoping to clarify things. It seems there are a couple styles of preprocessing:

```
      'cifarnet': cifarnet_preprocessing,
      'inception': inception_preprocessing,
      'resnet_v1_200': vgg_preprocessing,
```

As found in https://github.com/tensorflow/models/issues/2217 and https://github.com/tensorflow/models/tree/31adae5327c0258ce630f7b3e9f3cf0df78e3ba6/research/slim/preprocessing
